### Part 2: Fix WeatherMap Forecast Spacing (Correctly)

**Current Problem:**
```tsx
// Line 384: gap-2 pushes everything left
className="flex items-center gap-2 p-3 ..."
```

**Correct Fix:**
```tsx
// Use justify-between but reduce internal spacing
className="flex items-center justify-between p-2 ..." // Reduce padding p-3 → p-2

// Date: Keep narrower
min-w-[80px]  // ✅ This is good

// Icon: Reduce margin
mx-1  // ✅ This is good

// Temps: Keep tighter
gap-1.5  // ✅ This is good
```

**Result:** Items distributed across row, but with tighter internal spacing

### Part 3: Fix Map Drag Conflict (Proper Solution)

**Problem:** Map uses Leaflet, which handles its own drag events. When you drag the map, it bubbles up and triggers widget drag.

**Correct Solution:** Stop propagation on map container

**File:** `src/widgets/WeatherMap.tsx`
```tsx
// Add onMouseDown handler to map container
<div
  ref={mapRef}
  className="absolute inset-0 z-0"
  onMouseDown={(e) => e.stopPropagation()}  // ← Prevent drag bubbling
  onTouchStart={(e) => e.stopPropagation()} // ← For mobile
/>
```

**Result:** Map drag events don't bubble to widget drag handler

